<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,620,899]" box="[151,572,620,647]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,530,620,647]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Number of specimens recorded.</emphasis>
21.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,620,899]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,656,683]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Distribution.</emphasis>
Europe; also North Africa. 
<collectingCountry box="[676,775,657,683]" name="Portugal" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Portugal</collectingCountry>
: four northern provinces in this study, and Algarve (Dyte unpubl. data).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,620,899]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,729,755]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Ecology.</emphasis>
Although being collected in a variety of biotopes in 
<collectingCountry box="[890,988,729,755]" name="Portugal" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Portugal</collectingCountry>
, most of them encompassed riverbanks. In northwestern Europe, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haliday" authorityYear="1838" box="[426,545,765,791]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Dolichopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="signifer">
<emphasis box="[426,545,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">D. signifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
prefers muddy spots in open marshlands, in particular in salt marshes and brackish marshes (
<bibRefCitation author="Pollet, M." box="[297,432,801,827]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="1 - 190" refId="ref34362" refString="Pollet, M. (2000) A documented Red List of the dolichopodid flies (Diptera: Dolichopodidae) of Flanders [in Dutch with English summary]. Communications of the Institute of Nature Conservation, 8, 1 - 190." type="journal article" year="2000">Pollet 2000</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,620,899]" box="[199,768,836,863]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,836,863]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Rarity (%).</emphasis>
5.7 (fairly rare). Fairly common (FL).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,620,899]" box="[199,753,872,899]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,386,872,899]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Activity period.</emphasis>
April–July, September–October.
</paragraph>
